Google search terms:
- multilingual website
- (and others)

>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>> http://www.nomensa.com/blog/2010/7-tips-and-techniques-for-multi-lingual-website-accessibility

Include language in code of the page.
<html lang="en">
Do this for each page and each language.

>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>> http://stackoverflow.com/questions/15970948/how-to-develop-the-site-to-switch-between-multiple-languages

Make copies of each webpage, one in English and one in French.

>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>> http://everyday.marketing/getting-started-with-multilingual-websites/

Use utf-8 encoding.
<meta charset="UTF-8" />

Use URL like www.site.com/en/...
             www.site.com/fr/...

>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>> http://www.cre8asiteforums.com/forums/topic/20153-multi-language-site-how-to-organize-it/

Makes copies in both languages, so that Google can find either site (vs javascript or whatever).

>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>> http://www.wikihow.com/Organize-Files-on-a-Website

Put every webpage inside a separate folder, and call the file index.html.

Link to other pages using the folder:
<a href="www.site.com/puppies/">Puppies</a>
